Introduction

Hello Venus debuted as a six-member girl group in 2012 under the partnership between Pledis Entertainment and Fantagio. The group promoted for two years until Pledis Entertainment and Fantagio music went separate ways, which lead to a re-organization among members and the group itself. Yoo Ara and Yoonjo left the group, which prompted the addition of Seoyoung and Yeoreum.

Hello Venus continued to promote under Fantagio as a six-member group until their disbandment in 2019.
